metadata.value: Brown boards, 20th century.

metadata.label: Condition
metadata.value:
Staining to the opening endleaves (1r-3v) and occasional moisture-damage (16r-16v, 131r).

Most of the miniatures have been heavily rubbed and their pigments have flaked away (10v, 12v, 14v, 17v, 19v, 21v, 23v, 98v, 109v, 126v).

A few initials have been smudged (8v-9r, 92r).

Suffrages to St Thomas of Canterbury have been crossed out roughly (16r-16v, 36r).

metadata.value: 143 fols (foliated 1-143). Leaf height: 185 mm, width: 125 mm. Written height: 105-110 mm, width: 70 mm.

metadata.label: Abstract
metadata.value: An early example of a Book of Hours produced in Bruges for the English market. The Calendar lists Sts Donatian, Judoc, Basil and Eligius and the Litany includes 'S. Gheertrudis'. A London or Essex provenance is suggested by the memoria of St Ethelburga added in the early 15th century (16v). The miniatures were painted by the Master of the Beaufort Saints.

metadata.label: Collation
metadata.value:
The manuscript consists of 16 quires, mostly gatherings of 8 leaves and occasionally with miniatures inserted on additional single leaves. Quire 2 comprises numerous single leaves and its collation is irregular; the exact structure of the quire is uncertain. The structure of Quire 13 is also not clear. According to Binski and Zutshi, a miniature of St Jerome has been removed before 135r at the beginning of Quire 16, however it has not been possible to determine how this related to the collation of the volume.

  • 3 medieval parchment leaves (fols 1-3)
  • Quire 16 (fols 4-9)
  • Quire 2thirteen (fols 10-22)
  • Quire 38+1 (fols 23-31; 1st leaf inserted before f. 24)
  • Quires 4-58 (fols 32-47)
  • Quire 68+1 (fols 48-56; 4th leaf inserted after f. 50)
  • Quires 7-88 (fols 57-72)
  • Quire 98+2 (fols 73-82; 1st and 2nd leaves inserted before f. 75)
  • Quire 108(fols 83-90)
  • Quire 116+1 (fols 91-97; 1st leaf inserted before f. 92)
  • Quire 128+1 (fols 98-106; 1st leaf inserted before f. 99)
  • Quire 13eleven (fols 107-117)

metadata.value: MS Ff.6.8

metadata.label: Decoration
metadata.value:
Miniatures:

Thirteen (originally fifteen) full-page miniatures, framed by green, blue, orange, ochre or pink panels linked by gold quadrilobes and surrounded by short black sprays terminating in gold disks and ivy leaves.

  • 10v: Throne of Mercy ('Domine deus omnipotens')
  • 12v: Vernicle ('Salve sancta facies')
  • 14v: St John the Baptist ('Gaude Iohannes Baptista')
  • [before 16r: ?St Thomas of Canterbury; miniature removed ('Gaude lux londaniarum')]
  • 17v: St Christopher ('Sancte Cristofore')
  • 19v: St Catherine ('Gaude virgo Katherina')
  • 21v: St Mary Magdalene ('Gaude pia magdalena')
  • 23v: Annunciation (Matins of the Virgin)
  • 51v: Our Lady of Humility ('Salve virgo virginum')
  • 74v: Deposition (Hours of the Passion)
  • 91v: Man of Sorrows (Psalms of the Passion)
  • 98v: Last Judgement (Penitential Psalms)
  • 109v: funeral service (Office of the Dead)
  • 126v: Christ holding or blessing three souls carried to heaven by two angels ('Commendatio animarum')
  • [before 135r: ?St Jerome; miniature removed ('Beatus ieronimus')]


Initials:

Twenty-one three- to six-line initials with white ornamentation and blue, purple and orange floral scroll infill on burnished gold ground. At major textual divisions, initials are accompanied by four-sided frames of cusped burnished gold, purple and blue bars with short oak and ivy leaf scrolls and gold studded black sprays. At minor textual divisions, there are identical bars extending from purple-and-orange initials in the left-hand margins.

  • 24r, 28v, 39r, 41r, 42v, 44r, 45v, 46v: Hours of the Virgin.
  • 52r: 'Salve virgo virginum'.
  • 75r, 77v, 78v, 79v, 80v, 81v, 82v: Hours of the Passion.
  • 92r: Psalm 22.
  • 99r: Penitential Psalms.
  • 110r: Office of the Dead.
  • 127r: 'Commendatio animarum'.
  • 135r: Psalter of St Jerome.


Two- and three-line burnished gold initials with blue/purple infill and frames, to verses, prayers and in the Calendar. With gold, blue and purple bars with white patterns and short gold-studded black sprays extending from gold initials in left margins.


One- and two-line blue or gold initials with red or purple flourishes.


Capitals highlighted in red.

metadata.value: George I, King of Great Britain, 1660-1727

metadata.label: Additions
metadata.value: Computus texts and prayers added to endleaves and blank spaces within the manuscript, in Latin and Middle English. One of the additions, made in the early 15th century, is a memoria to St Ethelburga (16v).

metadata.label: Subject(s)
metadata.value: Graduals (Liturgical books)

metadata.label: Format
metadata.value: Codex

metadata.label: Layout
metadata.value:
Single column, 21 lines, ruled in red ink, below top line.

Calendar: single column, 34 lines, ruled in red ink, below top line.

metadata.label: Foliation
metadata.value: Modern pencil foliation in the top right corner of each leaf.
